timeline.bodyText:
The authentication object should be deserialised from the stream as well, i.e. authentication = new Authentication(in);.
Since this is a new field, which does not exist in previous version, we need to protect the read with version check, i.e.:
if (in.getVersion().onOrAfter(Version.V_7_10_0) {
    authentication = new Authentication(in);
}
Techically, I don't think class like OpenIdConnectAuthenticateResponse travel across nodes, so whether reader/writer interfaces are really necessary for them  is debatable. But that is a separate issue, for consistency, it's better to have it here. (Edit: in fact, given the presense of TransportClient in 7.x, these interfaces could still be actually necessary)

